ipe, G.A.T. and Babalobi, O.O. 2005. Development of a geo-informatics database of abattoirs in Ibadan, Nigeria for epizootiological surveillance. Vom Journal of Veterinary Science 1 (2) : 24-31.</p><p>Onyeka, L., Ogundipe, G.A.T. and Babalobi, O.O. 2006. Limitations to the development of a GIS - Based Abattoir Surveillance Database in Ibadan, Nigeria. 1st OIE International Conference on the Use of Geographical Information Systems (GIS) in Veterinary Activities, 8 -11 October 2006. Silvi Marina (TE), Abruzzo, Italy.</p><p>Onyeka, L. 2004. Development of Geographical Information Systems Data base for Disease Surveillance, Monitoring and Control: A Case Study. A Masters of Preventive Veterinary Medicine MPVM project submitted to the Department of Veterinary Public Health and Preventive Medicine, University of Ibadan, Ibadan, Nigeria. October 2004.</p><p>Oyelekan, O. and Olorundare, A. 2009. <a href="http://ijedict.dec.uwi.edu/viewarticle.php?id=677" target="_blank">Development and validation of a computer instructional package on electrochemistry for secondary schools in Nigeria</a>. International Journal of Education and Development using ICT, 5 (2) . </p><p>
